
[1]staurotide

   STAUROLITE, STAUROTIDE, n. [Gr., a cross, a stone.] The granatit of
   Werner or grenatite of Jameson; a mineral crystalized in prisms, either
   single or intersecting each other at right angles. Its color is white
   or gray, reddish or brown. It is often opake, sometimes translucent.
   Its form and infusibility distinguish it from the garnet. It is called
   by the French, harmotome.
